---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const lastUpdated = 'July 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`Privacy Policy | ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="How Sanpou handles your data. Nothing leaves your device except where explicitly described here."
		/>
		<style>
			main {
				width: 720px;
				max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
				margin: auto;
				padding: 3em 1em;
			}
			.meta {
				color: rgb(var(--gray));
				font-size: 0.9em;
				margin-bottom: 2em;
			}
			.lang-switch {
				float: right;
				font-size: 0.9em;
			}
			section {
				margin-bottom: 2em;
			}
			section h2 {
				font-size: 1.3em;
				margin-bottom: 0.4em;
			}
			p,
			li {
				color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
				line-height: 1.8;
			}
			ul {
				padding-left: 1.2em;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<a class="lang-switch" href={`${base}privacy/ja/`}>日本語</a>
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

			<section>
				<h2>The Short Version</h2>
				<p>
					Sanpou has no account system, no advertising, and no analytics. Your memos, photos,
					videos, audio recordings, and location history live on your device and are not uploaded
					to any server run by us. The two exceptions — speech recognition on older versions of
					iOS, and the feedback form — are described below.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>What Stays on Your Device</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Memo text, and the time each memo was created</li>
					<li>Photos, videos, and ambient audio attached to a memo</li>
					<li>The coordinates recorded with a memo, and your home spot</li>
					<li>Step counts read from Apple HealthKit</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					None of this is transmitted to a server we operate. It leaves your device only when you
					yourself export or share it — for example, exporting Markdown to iCloud Drive, or sending
					a memo through the iOS share sheet.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Speech Recognition</h2>
				<p>
					On iOS 26 and later, speech is transcribed entirely on your device. On earlier versions of
					iOS, Sanpou falls back to Apple's speech recognition service, which means the audio is
					sent to Apple and handled under Apple's privacy policy. We never receive it. This applies
					to live dictation as well as to transcription of ambient and conversation recordings. The
					recordings themselves, and the resulting memos, are stored only on your device.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Location</h2>
				<p>
					When you allow location access, Sanpou records the coordinates of a memo so it can be
					shown on the map, and so it can tell home from away. These coordinates are stored on your
					device and are not sent anywhere. You can revoke the permission at any time in iOS
					Settings; memos still work without it.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Health Data</h2>
				<p>
					Sanpou reads step counts from HealthKit to show your daily, weekly, monthly, and yearly
					totals, and to record how far you had walked when a memo was made. Step data is read
					only, stays on your device, and can be revoked at any time under Settings &gt; Privacy
					&amp; Security &gt; Health. Sanpou never writes to HealthKit.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Photos and Text Recognition</h2>
				<p>
					Photos and videos you attach are stored inside the app. When you extract text from a
					photo, recognition runs on your device through Apple's Vision framework. The image is not
					uploaded anywhere.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Feedback</h2>
				<p>
					If you send feedback from within the app, the submission is delivered to a Google Form
					owned by the developer. It contains the screen you were on, the category you chose, the
					text you wrote, your app version, your iOS version, and your language setting. It does not
					include your memos, photos, audio, or location. Sending feedback is always your choice.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>This Website</h2>
				<p>
					sanpou.mdaisuke.net uses Google Analytics to count visits and understand which pages are
					read. This is the website only — the app contains no analytics of any kind.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Third Parties</h2>
				<p>
					The app contains no advertising SDKs, no third-party analytics, and no data brokers. There
					is no account to create and nothing to log in to.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Children</h2>
				<p>
					Sanpou is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly collect information
					from them. Since no personal data is collected at all, there is nothing for us to hold.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Changes</h2>
				<p>
					This policy may be updated as the app changes. Any update is reflected in the "Last
					updated" date above.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Contact</h2>
				<p>
					Questions about this policy can be sent through the feedback form in the app, or through
					the App Store listing.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
